title: Coronavirus : What about animals & us?
text: With much worldwide concern for the Coronavirus outbreak in China, some have asked about Coronavirus in their animals. Without getting too deep, Corona is class of viruses with similar phenotypic traits, i.e. they look the same. But these Coronaviruses can be extremely different from mild to simple, not an issue.

og.title: Coronavirus : What about animals & us?
og.description: With much worldwide concern for the Coronavirus outbreak in China, some have asked about Coronavirus in their animals. Without getting too deep, Corona is class of viruses with similar phenotypic traits, i.e. they look the same. But these Coronaviruses can be extremely different from mild to simple, not an issue. So, I thought I’d take a quick spin though some of the animals you have and what if any are their Coronavirus issues. In dogs, we’ve said for years this is a “vaccine looking for a disease.” There’s no consensus whether this virus is even a pathogen. We used to think it was.
